Class Format

java.lang.Object
Format
public class Format extends Object
This class defines characters that correspond to the grammar format in a file and their LaTeX equivalents used for the parse tree in the output file.

Each rule must follow the format :

[ruleNumber] <variable> â†’ symbol1 <variable1> symbol2 <variable2> ...

where [ruleNumber] is the rule number, <variable1> <variable2> ... are variables symbols, and symbol1 symbol2 ... are terminals symbols.
